    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Young Arabs Who Hate Us</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Suzannah B Troy letter on Aug 15 editorial holds Arab leaders spur anti-American rage rather than using United States aid to help own people and economies</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your Aug. 15 editorial about the anger of Arab youths does not address their leaders' failure to allow the sometimes enormous amounts of money we hand over to Egypt and Saudi Arabia, to mention just two countries, to ''trickle down'' to the poor.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your Aug. 15 editorial about the anger of Arab youths does not address their leaders' failure to allow the sometimes enormous amounts of money we hand over to Egypt and Saudi Arabia, to mention just two countries, to ''trickle down'' to the poor.</p>
        <p>The United States is used as a scapegoat to rally angry and poor people. The Arab leaders encourage this anti-American rage, rather than helping their own people and economies.</p>
        <p>SUZANNAH B. TROY  New York, Aug. 15, 2002</p>
      </block>
